.TH "fcp_bus_reset" 9 "fcp_bus_reset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fcp_bus_reset \- inform the target handler about a bus reset
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" fcp_bus_reset
.BI "(struct fw_unit *unit "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "unit" 12
the unit that might be used by \fBfcp_avc_transaction\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function must be called from the driver's .update handler to inform
the FCP transaction handler that a bus reset has happened.  Any pending FCP
transactions are retried.
